name: Walmart DEI policies
summary: Amid growing conservative backlash, Walmart, the largest private employer in the US, has joined a trend of companies rolling back their diversity, equity, and inclusion (DEI) policies. These policies aimed to promote diverse hiring and workplace practices, but have faced criticism for allegedly privileging certain groups and undermining meritocracy. Walmart's CEO claims the policy changes will make all customers feel welcome, indicating a shift in focus from specific DEI initiatives to a broader commitment to inclusivity. This move aligns with similar decisions by other major companies, such as Toyota, who have faced pressure from conservative groups and accusations of unfairness in hiring and promotion practices. The rollback of DEI policies has sparked debate about the importance of diversity and inclusion in the workplace and the role of corporations in promoting social justice.

summary: It has been announced that 'Vanderpump Rules' will be returning for a 12th season with a brand-new cast. The show, which follows the lives of young adults working at Lisa Vanderpump's restaurants in West Hollywood, has been on hiatus for two years following the firing of several cast members over their involvement in the "Scandoval," a racist social media scandal. The upcoming season will feature an entirely new group of SURvers, with the exception of Lisa Vanderpump herself. This wholesale cast change is a significant departure from previous seasons, and it remains to be seen how the new cast will be received by viewers.
